Column Comment.0: STORE ID: Unique identifier for the data store location.
Column Comment.1: ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating whether this row of data is currently eitheractive / valid (Y) or inactive / invalid (N).
Column Comment.2: ADDRESS OBSERVATION NUMBER: A number used to uniquely identifying anaddress for a Business Associate.
Column Comment.3: ADDRESS SOURCE: The source of the BA Address used.
Column Comment.4: BUSINESS ASSOCIATE: Unique identifier for a business associate, such as aperson, company, regulatory agency, government or consortium.
Column Comment.5: STORE ID: Unique identifier for the data store location.
Column Comment.6: DATA STORE HIERARCHY IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for a hierarchy thatdefines how a data store is structured.
Column Comment.7: DATA STORE NAME: The name given to the storage facility. May be a buildingname , Bay name or a directory or file name.
Column Comment.8: DATA STORE TYPE: the type of data store that is referenced, such as disk, folder,tape, shelf, SAN system server or optical disk.
Column Comment.9: EFFECTIVE DATE: The date that the data in this row first came into effect.
Column Comment.10: EXPIRY DATE: The date that the data in this row was no longer active or in effect.
Column Comment.11: HIERARCHY LEVEL IDENTIFIER: A unique identifier assigned to a level in aplanned hierarchy. Note that a hierarchy may contain more than one branch.
Column Comment.12: LOCATION ID: A location ID already assigned to the physical item. May be a barcode or a legacy system Identifier.
Column Comment.13: LONG DESCRIPTION: A long description of the storage location
Column Comment.14: PHYSICAL STORE STATUS: The current status of this physical data store, such asoperating, closed, destroyed etc.
Column Comment.15: ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global uniqueidentifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used,optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the datamodel DDL should be created.
Column Comment.16: REMARK: Narrative remarks about this row of data.
Column Comment.17: SHORT DESCRIPTION: short description of the storage location.
Column Comment.18: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.19: TOTAL CAPACITY: the total number of data store units that are available in this one,such as the number of slots on a rack, or the number of shelving slots in a bay. Usedto determine how full a data store is.
Column Comment.20: USED CAPACITY: the total number of data store units in this one that are currentlyfilled, and unavailable for use.
Column Comment.21: USED CAPACITY DATE: The date that the used capacity was last calculated.
Column Comment.22: ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.
Column Comment.23: ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.
Column Comment.24: ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.
Column Comment.25: ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.
Column Comment.26: ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of datais effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data wasmade available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.27: ROW_EXPIRY_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data isno longer effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row ofdata was no longer available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.28: PPDM ROW QUALITY: A set of values indicating the quality of data in this row,usually with reference to the method or procedures used to load the data, althoughother types of quality reference are permitted.
